    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="1658"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1658">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.6712/9.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State ad interim</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Chargé d’Affaires of Turkey</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 25.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith a copy of a
                    despatch of the 1st instant from the American Consul at Aguascalientes reporting
                    that at the request of the firm of S. Bujdud Hermano and Jalife, Ottoman
                    subjects, he has obtained the release of ninety-four bales of cotton which had
                    been sequestered by the Mexican Government.</p>
                <p>I should be glad to be informed whether the Embassy has any advices concerning
                    the report contained in the despatch as to the designation of the German Consul
                    at San Luis Potosí to care for Ottoman interests.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
